// rejected: the function-return arrow `->` is RETIRED (RFC-0037 D4 — the arrow is now `=>`). The
// `->` glyph still lexes (it is the operator-desugaring arrow token), so the parser gives an explicit
// teaching refusal at the return-arrow position rather than silently accepting the old form (G2). A
// retired surface form is never silently accepted.
nodule bad;
fn f(x: Binary{8}) -> Binary{8} = x
